      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Expecting well-bred filly KAHULA (10) to progress off her debut performance in the heats where she settled back and warmed up late for second. Starts from the same draw and may require some luck but she looks to have talent and expect the Stewart camp to have her wound up for finals night. SHES A DELANEY (8) had 8m on KAHULA when winning their heat but she did take advantage of the ace draw to lead throughout. Tougher task from this barrier but she is building a handy record having also landed the Pink Bonnet at Menangle two back and she has the pace to push forward from out wide. DECOUPAGE (3) came from wider to place behind the top two selections in the heat and also drew deep when second to SHES A DELANEY on debut in the Pink Bonnet. She'll enjoy the lowest draw she has had in her career so far. ATOMIK GO ANNA (11) draws on the back row again but she won from there two back at Bathurst and was solid last week. Has some upside so include.",
